<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section 3311 prohibits the operation of a vessel subject to inspection without having on board a valid certificate of inspection.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idf66292ae-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idf66292af-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1984—<ref href="/us/pl/98/498">Pub. L. 98–498</ref> designated existing provisions as subsec. (a), substituted “Except as provided in subsection (b), a vessel” for “A vessel”, struck out “valid” before “certificate of inspection”, and added subsec. (b).</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idf66292b0-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idf66292b1-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="1984-04-15">Apr. 15, 1984</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/98/89/s2/g/1">section 2(g)(1) of Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s3101">section 3101 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
